<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id121e2987-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s705"><num value="705">§ 705.</num><heading> Duplicate orders to print</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Government Publishing Office shall examine the orders of the Senate and House of Representatives for printing, and in case of duplication shall print under the first order received.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id121e2988-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1248">82 Stat. 1248</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/235/dH/tI/s1301/c/1">Pub. L. 113–235, div. H, title I, § 1301(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-16">Dec. 16, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2537">128 Stat. 2537</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id121e2989-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id121e298a-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 135 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s53">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 53</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/608">28 Stat. 608</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id121e298b-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id121e298c-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/235">Pub. L. 113–235</ref> substituted “Director of the Government Publishing Office” for “Public Printer”.</p>
</note>
